{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsRAZWnxYuoeAp2rfBU8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Given `data` is `emptyDir` (not persisted), a naive rolling image bump risks data loss once nodes cross into 4.x — RabbitMQ 4.x removes classic queue mirroring, so the last node to upgrade would hold the only copy with no mirror to protect it during its own restart. My plan:\n\n1. Roll to 3.13 first (required intermediate hop — mirroring still fully works node-to-node here).\n2. While still on 3.13, migrate storage from `emptyDir` to PVC-backed (one node at a time, protected by mirroring).\n3. Roll to 4.1 — now each node's data persists across its own restart via PVC, so no reliance on cross-node mirroring is needed for that last, risky hop.\n\nLet me check for a default StorageClass first, since that's needed for step 2."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":456,"cache_read_input_tokens":72519,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":456},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"135ba1af-e67b-4bf2-b6be-9227c70336db","uuid":"889b1e54-db82-4551-b85b-260a3af676d9","request_id":"req_011CcsRAYDAESYxHEG73xHjU"}
