{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsRtPNmUbNfqbLpiifq3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This confirms a genuine data-loss incident: the rolling 3.12→3.13 upgrade caused every node to fail rejoining the live cluster (feature-flag incompatibility during peer discovery on blank/ephemeral storage), so all `/app`/`/ops` vhosts, users, permissions, and the `app-queue` messages were lost. I need to flag this clearly, then remediate. Let me check what created the original setup so I can restore the structure correctly, and check the current split-cluster state."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5952,"cache_read_input_tokens":115781,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5952},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"135ba1af-e67b-4bf2-b6be-9227c70336db","uuid":"2477c286-ed1c-4afc-b01f-328d83a16d02","request_id":"req_011CcsRtN3ttkrki9WYAM8E7"}
